# StockAnalysis Project

## Project Overview
This is a stock analysis website that hosts AI-generated HTML analysis reports for US stocks. The site has a main landing page (`index.html`) that lists and links to individual stock reports.

## GitHub Repository
- URL: https://github.com/charithadc/StockAnalysis
- Remote: `origin` -> `https://github.com/charithadc/StockAnalysis`

## Project Structure
```
index.html              <- main landing page listing all stock reports
reports/
  FERG/  -> FERG_Analysis_Report.html, FERG_Analysis_Report_V2.html
  FIX/   -> FIX_Analysis_Report.html
  LPLA/  -> LPLA_Analysis_Report.html, LPLA_Analysis_Report_V2.html, LPLA_Analysis_Report_V3.html
  LRCX/  -> LRCX_Analysis_Report.html, LRCX_Analysis_Report_V2.html
  MSFT/  -> MSFT_Analysis_Report_2026.html, MSFT_Analysis_Report.html, MSFT_Analysis_Report_V3.html
  TGLS/  -> TGLS_Analysis_Report_V3.html
  VISA/  -> VISA_Analysis_Report.html, Visa_V_Stock_Analysis_Report.html
```

## Conventions
- Report files: `{TICKER}_Analysis_Report.html` (V1) and `{TICKER}_Analysis_Report_V2.html` (V2)
- Each new stock gets its own subfolder: `reports/{TICKER}/`
- Version badge rules in index.html:
  - V2 (latest version of a ticker): `<span class="version-badge latest">V2</span>`
  - V1 (original version): `<span class="version-badge">V1</span>`
  - Only one version exists: `<span class="version-badge latest">V1</span>`
  - Do NOT use "Enhanced" or any other made-up label

## Adding a New Report (ALWAYS follow this process)
When the user provides a new HTML report file:
1. Copy the file into `reports/{TICKER}/` (create the folder if new ticker)
2. Insert ONLY the new card into index.html using PowerShell -- do NOT regenerate the whole file
3. Use this PowerShell pattern to insert the new card before the first existing <article tag:
   ```
   $p = "...index.html"
   $html = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText($p, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false))
   $newCard = @' ...card HTML... '@
   $html = $html.Replace('    <!-- FIRST_CARD_COMMENT -->', $newCard + '    <!-- FIRST_CARD_COMMENT -->')
   [System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($p, $html, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false))
   ```
4. Verify 0 null bytes after writing
5. Update the Project Structure section in this rules file to include the new file

## Key Notes
- This is a Windows machine running PowerShell -- use `;` instead of `&&` to chain shell commands
- The project uses plain HTML/CSS (no build tools or frameworks)
- Reports are standalone HTML files with embedded styles and scripts

## Critical Rule -- Self-Contained Files
Every HTML file must be fully self-contained -- all CSS and JS embedded inside using `<style>` and `<script>` tags.
Never extract to external files. A single file must work standalone in any browser.

## CRITICAL -- File Encoding (MUST FOLLOW EVERY TIME)
The Cursor Write tool AND StrReplace tool save files as UTF-16 on this Windows machine (null bytes between chars). Browsers cannot render UTF-16 HTML.

NEVER use Write tool or StrReplace tool on HTML files. ALWAYS use PowerShell to read/write files:

  $p = "FULL_FILE_PATH"
  $html = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllText($p, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false))
  # modify $html in PowerShell
  [System.IO.File]::WriteAllText($p, $html, (New-Object System.Text.UTF8Encoding $false))

Verify: ($bytes = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes($p); ($bytes | Where-Object {$_ -eq 0}).Count) must be 0.